description.narrative: In 2019, the key highlight is the adoption of the Global Education Strategy and the ECARO efforts to support its implementation as part of the regional education agenda and through the support to country offices. The key shifts included: strong focus on learning for all children and at all levels of education, through increased engagement in evidence-based policy making, such as education sector analysis and planning, and use of innovation and technology to design and scale up effective solutions aimed at improving children's learning outcomes, especially for the most disadvantaged children. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:03/02/2020
